SVD
A\in\mathbb R^{m\times n}
\textrm{rank}(A)=k
A
 \displaystyle A^\dagger=\sum_{i=1}^k\sigma_i^{-1}v_iu_i^T. 
{\bf Proof:}
AA^\dagger A=A
A^\dagger AA^\dagger=A^\dagger
(A^\dagger A)^T=A^\dagger A
(AA^\dagger)^T=AA^\dagger
A
\tilde{\Sigma}=\textrm{diag}(\sigma_1, \ldots, \sigma_k)
A=U_1\tilde{\Sigma}V_1^T
A^\dagger=V_1\tilde{\Sigma}^{-1}U_1^T
V^TV=U^TU=I
U_1^TU_1=V_1^TV_1=I
(AA^\dagger)=I=AA^\dagger
A^\dagger A=AA^\dagger=I
A
{\bf Problems:}
(A^\dagger A)=I
A
A=U\Sigma V^T
A=U\Sigma V
V^TV=I_n
U^TU=I_m
n=m
I_n\neq I_m
U_1^T U_1=I_k=V_1^T V_1
\begin{align} A^\dagger\,A & =V_1\tilde \Sigma^{-1} U_1^T U_1\tilde \Sigma V_1^T\\ &=V_1\tilde \Sigma^{-1} I_k\tilde \Sigma V_1^T\\ &=V_1\tilde \Sigma^{-1} \tilde \Sigma V_1^T\\ &=V_1 I_k V_1^T\\ &=V_1 V_1^T\\ &=\left[\begin{array}{c|c} I_k&0\\ \hline 0&0 \end{array}\right] \end{align}\,.
